## ðŸ” `setInterval()` â€“ "Repeat again and again"

### âœ… What it does:

> Runs the function **again and again** every time the interval passes.

### ðŸ“¦ Syntax:

```js
setInterval(() => {
  // code to run again and again
}, 1000); // every 1 second
```

### ðŸ§ª Example:

```js
setInterval(() => {
  console.log("Tick");
}, 1000);
```

âœ… Output:

```
Tick   (after 1 sec)
Tick   (after 2 sec)
Tick   (after 3 sec)
... and so on
```

---

## âŒ How to Stop Them

### ðŸ”» `clearTimeout(timerId)`

* Stops a **scheduled timeout** from running.

### ðŸ” `clearInterval(timerId)`

* Stops a **repeating interval** from running.

---

### ðŸ§ª Example: Stop a timer

```js
const timeoutId = setTimeout(() => {
  console.log("This will not run");
}, 5000);

clearTimeout(timeoutId); // âŒ stops the above before it runs
```

---

### ðŸ§ª Example: Stop a repeating interval

```js
const intervalId = setInterval(() => {
  console.log("Ticking...");
}, 1000);

setTimeout(() => {
  clearInterval(intervalId); // â›” stop it after 5 seconds
  console.log("Stopped ticking");
}, 5000);
```

âœ… Output:

```
Ticking...
Ticking...
Ticking...
Ticking...
Ticking...
Stopped ticking
```

